==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Freyr
<hw>Freyr</hw></mhw> <pr>(fr⟦imac⟧)</pr>, <pos>prop.
n.</pos> <fld>(Norse Mythology)</fld> <def>The god of earth's fertility
and peace and prosperity, presiding over rain, sunshine, and all the
fruits of the earth, dispensing wealth among men; son of Njorth (Njord)
and brother of Freya; originally of the Vanir; later with the Aesir. He
was especially worshipped in the temple at Upsala in Sweden</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> + <source>Century Dict. 1906</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freya</ent>⟦br⟧
